org.xandercat.pmdb.service

Interface MovieService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MovieServiceImpl

    public interface MovieService
    Service interface for the management of movies. CollectionSharingException can be thrown from most methods if action being performed requires permission on a collection the calling user does not have. WebServicesExceptions can be thrown from most methods if cloud functions are required but cloud services are disabled or otherwise unavailable.
    Author:
    Scott Arnold

      • searchMoviesForCollection

        Set<Movie> searchMoviesForCollection(String collectionId,
                                     String searchString,
                                     String callingUsername)
                              throws CollectionSharingException,
                                     WebServicesException
        Search the movie collection of given id for the given search string. The search string is case insensitive and can be part of the movie title or part of any attribute value associated with the movie.
        Parameters:
        collectionId - movie collection id
        searchString - search string
        callingUsername - user making the call
        Returns:
        movies matching the provided search string
        Throws:
        CollectionSharingException - if user does not have permission to perform the operation
        WebServicesException - if a web service failure occurs

      • reorderTableColumnPreference

        void reorderTableColumnPreference(int sourceIdx,
                                  int targetIdx,
                                  String username)
                           throws PmdbException
        Reorder existing table column preference from given source index. If target index is greater than source index, attribute will be moved after the given target index, and those in between are moved up. If target index is less than source index, attribute will be moved before the given target index, and those in between are moved down.
        Parameters:
        sourceIdx - index of the preference to move.
        targetIdx - target index (not necessarily the final index of the attribute)
        username - user to change preference for
        Throws:
        PmdbException - if sourceIdx or targetIdx are out of range

      • deleteTableColumnPreference

        void deleteTableColumnPreference(int sourceIdx,
                                 String username)
        Remove attribute name from those that should be included in the movie table on the home page. Attribute name is referenced by it's order index in the list of attribute names that are included in the table.
        Parameters:
        sourceIdx - index of attribute name within the list of attribute names that are included in the movie table.
        username - user making the call
